CNCP v1 23123
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13056: Nullish dynamic event name with a modifier creates attribute with modifier's name",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:08.849805+00:00",
  "text": "Nullish dynamic event name with a modifier creates attribute with modifier's name\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.13\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://codepen.io/markrian/pen/OPJmmoW\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Write a dynamic event binding with a modifier, e.g., `@[eventName].once=\"onEvent\"`.\n2. Set `eventName` to an empty value, like `null`, `undefined` or empty string.\n3. Notice that the modifier name is written as an attribute on the element.\n\nFor example:\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e418353b-7ba9-4d0b-8b84-b3d0dd7b7bfa)\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe modifier name should _not_ become an attribute on the element.\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b8af40f0-7057-4744-adb5-1db0651d580f)\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nThe modifier name becomes an attribute on the element, e.g., \n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a8301265-69c8-4fe7-ad53-00ef14196c09)\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n[Vue 2.7.16 behaves as expected](https://codepen.io/markrian/pen/OPJQRPy), i.e., does not create an attribute.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
